Great! For maintainability and performance, it’s best to create the BlobServiceClient only once and share it across your code. The ideal way is to place it in a singleton-style utility class.

⸻

✅ Recommended: Separate Utility Class

Here’s a clean and reusable Java utility class to create and reuse BlobServiceClient and BlobContainerClient.

⸻

🔧 BlobClientProvider.java

package com.yourcompany.utils;

import com.azure.storage.blob.*;
import com.azure.storage.blob.specialized.BlobLeaseClient;
import com.azure.storage.blob.specialized.BlobLeaseClientBuilder;
import com.azure.core.util.Configuration;

public class BlobClientProvider {

    private static BlobServiceClient blobServiceClient = null;

    // Initialize only once
    private static BlobServiceClient getBlobServiceClient() {
        if (blobServiceClient == null) {
            synchronized (BlobClientProvider.class) {
                if (blobServiceClient == null) {
                    String connectionString = Configuration.getGlobalConfiguration()
                        .get("AzureWebJobsStorage");

                    blobServiceClient = new BlobServiceClientBuilder()
                        .connectionString(connectionString)
                        .buildClient();
                }
            }
        }
        return blobServiceClient;
    }

    // Get container client
    public static BlobContainerClient getContainerClient(String containerName) {
        return getBlobServiceClient().getBlobContainerClient(containerName);
    }

    // Get blob client
    public static BlobClient getBlobClient(String containerName, String blobName) {
        return getContainerClient(containerName).getBlobClient(blobName);
    }

    // Optional: Get lease client
    public static BlobLeaseClient getBlobLeaseClient(BlobClient blobClient) {
        return new BlobLeaseClientBuilder()
            .blobClient(blobClient)
            .buildClient();
    }
}


⸻

✅ Usage Example (in any class)

BlobClient blobClient = BlobClientProvider.getBlobClient("my-container", "some-id-latest.json");
BlobLeaseClient leaseClient = BlobClientProvider.getBlobLeaseClient(blobClient);


